IMO this course of action puts them in an even worse position.If cigarette companies responded to health studies with a fancy new filter and were careful to make no mention of the fact that smoking was still fundamentally bad for you, they'd be hammered for it. Rightly. Even if they never actually say the new filter makes cigarettes safe, the combined implication is grossly irresponsible.Honesty and full disclosure seems like a sounder legal strategy if something is dangerous and you can't really mitigate that danger.
